  ('Turtle Bros','Backbounce 180 spin backbounce','5','2025-03-10 11:11:31','2023-01-30','Gon Caturelli','From backbounce gran the line behind your head, pull so you start spinning on a horizontal axis. End facing the other anchor in backbounce',null,'https://www.instagram.com/reel/CoCwNEPDmd1/','BACK','BACK'),
  ('Llamarada Yisus','Resurrection 180','7','2025-03-10 11:13:50','2023-01-30','Gon Caturelli','From yisus do a resurrection motion but add a 180 to land on your feet.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/reel/CoCwNEPDmd1/','YISUS','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Tortuga Koreana / korean turtle','Backbounce 360 spin to korean','6','2025-03-10 11:20:10','2023-04-12','Gon Caturelli','From backbounce grab the line behind your head and do a 360 spin to end in korean.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/reel/Cq8MTfKum12/','BACK','KOREAN'),
  ('Shoulder resurrection','Shoulder resurrection','7','2025-03-10 11:30:21','2023-07-31','Gon Caturelli','From shoulder go to yisus and from there do a resurrection',null,'https://www.instagram.com/reel/CvXWB58sjX4/','SHOULDER','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Rocket Orbital to Feet',null,'7','2025-03-11 20:21:01','2024-05-21','Ian Eisenberg','From Rocket Mount you do the second half of the Orbital motion and land to feet.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C7PGtbltFCM/','ROCKET','EXPOSURE'),
  ('FS 540 Rocket Mount',null,'8','2025-03-11 20:31:30','2024-06-29','Ian Eisenberg','There are multiple ways to do this one, but one version is to do a Full Rocket followed by a Rocket 180 to Feet, meaning that the first 360 spin you do with the line at chest height and then go to feet on the finishing 180.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C8zNkF0sWpo/','ROCKET','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Reverse Rocket Mount Late 180',null,'6','2025-03-11 20:34:55','2024-06-30','Ian Eisenberg','Reverse Rocket Mount but just before putting both feet on the line as you would normally, spin 180 and land in Expo.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C817747Mly3/','ROCKET','EXPOSURE'),
  ('5Nasty','540 Sick Nasty','6','2025-03-11 20:37:27','2024-06-30','Ian Eisenberg','Begin with a Tre-Nasty but then regrab with your hands and add another 180 in the end.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C817747Mly3/','SOFA','SOFA'),
  ('MasterVader','360 Double Darth Vader','9','2025-03-11 20:43:07','2024-07-08','Ian Eisenberg','360 Darth Vader followed by another roll to feet',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C9U2gAVMFz6/','ROCKET','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Shoulder Prawn','King Prawn to Shoulder','7','2025-03-11 20:51:03','2024-08-22','Ian Eisenberg','King Prawn to Shoulder',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C--bsTgiSON/','ROCKET','SHOULDER'),
  ('Spork','Cork 540 Space Orbital to Feet','9','2025-03-11 21:05:30','2024-11-07','Ian Eisenberg','...',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/DCFUuNAO2zK/','STAND','STAND'),
  ('Double Shoulder Vader',null,'9','2025-03-11 21:13:43','2024-09-20','Ian Eisenberg','ShoulderVader with an additional roll.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/DGTgGw4sJyp/','SHOULDER','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Shoulder Frontflip','Shoulder Frontroll to Shoulder','4','2025-03-18 07:52:17','2022-11-18','Sebastian Egger','From Shoulder do a Frontroll but don''t stop in Korean but keep going to land in Shoulder.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/Craw32qgRH3/','SHOULDER','SHOULDER'),
  ('Backbounce Spiral','360 Backbounce to Backbounce','5','2025-03-18 07:59:23','2022-12-18','Sebastian Egger','From Backbounce grab the line with one hand below your back and step on the line with the opposite foot. Turn towards the chest and swap both your hands and feet to be able to finish the full rotation.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/CnXOzwgK3qb/','BACK','BACK'),
  ('Lasagna Flip','Hammock Backroll from Feet to Feet','9','2025-03-18 08:05:03','2024-02-02','Sebastian Egger','Start with an early Hammock Roll from Feet and just when you finished the Hammock Roll part you add a Backroll to Feet.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C25OqhrM8zh/','STAND','STAND'),
  ('Dislocator','Dislocate Resurrection','6','2025-03-18 08:09:25','2024-06-19','Sebastian Egger','Drop to Dislocate and finish the trick like you would for a Resurrection','Make sure your shoulders are ready for it! First try it statically from Rocket, then drop in from Sofa and only when this feels safe you can start trying from feet.','https://www.instagram.com/p/C8aFBqrMHZc/','ROCKET','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Shoulder Roll Frontroll to Feet',null,'8','2025-03-18 08:12:54','2024-06-18','Sebastian Egger','Start with a Shoulder Roll then add a Frontroll to Feet.',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C85JKKtMsy4/','SHOULDER','STAND'),
  ('FS 180 Shoulder Spin',null,'5','2025-03-18 08:16:13','2024-08-18','Sebastian Egger','Spin 180 on your shoulder. You first have to regrab the far hand then to finish on the other shoulder you have to regrab the close hand (which on the other shoulder is now the far hand).',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C-qfaMXS70_/','SHOULDER','SHOULDER'),
  ('FS 360 Shoulder Spin',null,'7','2025-03-18 08:19:39','2024-05-15','Sebastian Egger','Watch the video...',null,'https://www.instagram.com/p/C-5Bp3My3vw/','SHOULDER','SHOULDER'),
  ('360 Nevermind Roll to Feet',null,'8','2025-03-18 08:24:36','2024-09-12','Sebastian Egger','Nevermind with a roll and a 360 ending in Expo.',null,'https://youtu.be/r6hcjIbrbr8?t=229','NEVERMIND','EXPOSURE'),
  ('FS 540 Nevermind',null,'8','2025-03-18 08:26:34','2024-09-19','Sebastian Egger','Nevermind with a FS 540 spin.',null,'https://youtu.be/r6hcjIbrbr8?t=236','NEVERMIND','EXPOSURE'),
  ('NH BS 180 Backflip',null,'8','2025-03-18 08:29:37','2024-09-20','Sebastian Egger','180 Backflip but without using your hands',null,'https://youtu.be/r6hcjIbrbr8?t=263','STAND','STAND'),
  ('Rewind Yo-Yo','Leash Rewind to Rocket Mount','8','2025-03-18 08:38:24','2025-09-19','Sebastian Egger','You drop to a leashfall and in the bottom of the bounce you wind yourself up in the leash then unwind again and use the momentum to get back up to the line. Finish in Expo.','You should probably wear a cup to protect your genitals (males and females!).
Having a shorter leash for this trick helps.','https://youtu.be/r6hcjIbrbr8?t=281','LEASH','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Reverse Rewind Yo-Yo','Leash Rewind to Reverse Rocket Mount','9','2025-03-18 08:42:22','2024-09-19','Sebastian Egger','Drop to a leashfall and in the bottom of the bounce you wind yourself up in the leash, then unwind again and use the momentum to get back up to the line. Finish with a Reverse Rocket Mount.','You should probably wear a cup to protect your genitals (males and females!).
A short leash helps for this trick.','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=r6hcjIbrbr8&t=300s','LEASH','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Robinspin','Triple Can of Soup','9','2025-04-14 20:27:40','2025-03-26','Jordan Robinson','Three rolls from soup to standing in one bounce.','Doing the trick chongo-style with a down leg for all three rotations lets you use that leg to huck each time you come around.','https://www.youtube.com/shorts/Zch-UMRZAhc','SOUP','STAND'),
  ('Misty Spin Roll','Is a Ddk 360 BS to spiral (360) to chest','6','2025-06-25 04:01:14','2025-06-20','José Perales','Is a ddk 360 BS to other Spin like a spiral in trickline under line to chest','Stay on the opposite side of the ddk to start the second turn below the line, all in one turn.',null,'DOUBLE DROPKNEE','CHEST'),
  ('Quad Back Yoda',null,'10','2025-08-30 17:02:01','2025-08-01','Davis Hermes','Four Back Yodas in one bounce. Sounds hard right? It is!',null,null,'EXPOSURE','EXPOSURE'),
  ('Doombringer','Panic Roll to Darkside Roll in the same bounce. Could also be considered a Panic Roll Rewind to Feet.','8','2025-11-01 20:15:36','2025-08-30','Jordan Robinson','Do a Panic Roll and set up for a Darkside Roll out of it. Similar to a Bangarang but starting with a Panic Roll.','The Panic Roll should be as fast as you can muster without the rotational force opening up your legs so that you can''t get them on the line. I try to aim to get my feet on the line as quickly as possible so that I have something to pull against for the second half. Hand positioning for the Panic Roll is super wide so that there''s space to fit the legs in between them.

The leash ring is best left between the legs but with the leash rope wrapped around the back of your leg so that you unwrap it during the Panic Roll. This will make it so that on the Darkside Roll portion of the trick the leash ring/rope is outside of your hands and completely out of the way of your feet as you sneak them onto the line.

If you''re slow with getting your second foot up for the Darkside portion you''ll end up imbalanced in the direction of the line and can fall sideways into it like an overhooked Almighty.

For me this trick took 7 bounces minimum.',null,'SOFA','EXPOSURE'),
  ('360 holy grail',null,'9.5','2025-12-23 10:30:48','2025-12-14','Lukas Blenkinsopp','Start with a 360 almighty as you complete the first rotation reach down and grab the line and do a front barrel/yoda','Focus on grabbing the line as you do the almighty so that you are grabbing the line as you come around on the top almighty to whip the barrel around quickly',null,'STAND','STAND'),
  ('Sick nastyroll and Nevermid','From korean sick nastyroll to Nevermid','6','2025-12-25 16:17:29','2025-12-22','José Perales','From korean sick nastyroll to Nevermid','Step on it hard',null,'KOREAN','NEVERMIND'),
  ('Fire Mind','Back Korean 180 roll to Nevermid','6','2025-12-25 16:41:57','2025-12-22','José Perales','From Korean, rotate backward, taking the line, making a roll, and following that roll into the Nevermid stance, ending in feet.','Step on it hard',null,'KOREAN','NEVERMIND'),
  ('Korean 180',null,'1',now(),null,null,'From Korean grab the line with both hands in front of you. Towards the top of the bounce swing one leg over the line so that you end up in the belly position. Then swing the other leg over the line so that you are back in Korean, only facing the other direction this time.','If it is hard to get the first leg over the line, try starting later in the bounce;As a preexercise you can practice the transition from Korean to Belly and vice verse in isolation before putting them together;','https://www.youtube.com/watch?v=3GWR5ZzSRBg','KOREAN','KOREAN')
) as t(given_name,technical_name,difficulty_tier,date_submitted,date_performed,
       original_performer,description,tips,video_link,start_pos,end_pos)
left join pos sp on sp.name = t.start_pos
left join pos ep on ep.name = t.end_pos;